dataDictionary.Title: PDS4 Data Dictionary
dataDictionary.Description: This document is a dump of the contents of the PDS4 Data Dictionary

class.title: Dawn
class.description: The Dawn class is the container for Dawn mission-specific metadata elements.

class.title: FC
class.description: The Dawn "FC" class is the container for Dawn Framing Camera (FC) specific metadata elements.

class.title: Frame_Parameters
class.description: The Frame_Parameters class contains attributes describing the acquisition of the VIR frames.

class.title: Scan_Parameters
class.description: The Scan_Parameters class contains attributes describing the activity of the VIR scan mirror.

class.title: TELREADOUT
class.description: A single scaler accumulation interval, and the first and last records and SCLKs for which the interval was in effect.

class.title: TELREADOUT_List
class.description: A list of scaler accumulation intervals, along with the records for which they were in effect.

class.title: TELSOH
class.description: A single state-of-health accumulation interval, and the first and last records and SCLKs for which the interval was in effect.

class.title: TELSOH_List
class.description: A list of state-of-health accumulation intervals, along with the records for which they were in effect.

class.title: VIR
class.description: The Dawn "VIR" class is the container for Dawn Visual and Infrared Spectrometer (VIR) specific metadata elements.

class.title: VIR_Instrument_Temperatures
class.description: The VIR_Instrument_Temperatures class contains attributes which identify the temperature in different sections of the VIR instrument.

class.title: VIR_Operational_Parameters
class.description: The VIR_Operational_Parameters contains attributes related to VIR operating mode information, data quality and other similar metadata.

attribute.title: mission_phase_name
attribute.description: The mission_phase_name attribute provides the mission-defined name of a mission phase.

attribute.title: spacecraft_clock_start_count
attribute.description: The spacecraft_clock_start_count attribute provides the value of the spacecraft clock at the beginning of a time period of interest.

attribute.title: spacecraft_clock_stop_count
attribute.description: The spacecraft_clock_stop_count attribute provides the value of the spacecraft clock at the beginning of a time period of interest.

attribute.title: standard_data_product_id
attribute.description: The standard_data_product_id keyword is used to identify data products of the same processing level that are not otherwise indentified by being in different collections within the bundle.

attribute.title: alt_start_time
attribute.description: The same time as the start_date_time attribute expressed year/day-of-year rather than year/month/day.

attribute.title: alt_stop_time
attribute.description: The same time as the stop_date_time attribute expressed year/day-of-year rather than year/month/day.

attribute.title: callamp_delay_time
attribute.description: Callamp switch on delay measured in microseconds after START_TIME. Callamp can be switched on before (less than 193000 s), at (= 193000 s), or after (greater than 193000 s) begin of exposure.

attribute.title: callamp_duty
attribute.description: The callamp can be run at various duty cycles between 0.0 % and 100.0 % by using only every other pulse of the callamp frequency to trigger the callamp. DAWN_CALLAMP_DUTY = CALLAMP_FREQUENCY / Value * 100 % Example: Value = 1.0 : DAWN_CALLAMP_DUTY = 100 % Value = 2.5 : DAWN_CALLAMP_DUTY = 40 % This calculation is done internally in the camera, the user commands the requensted duty cycle in percentage.

attribute.title: callamp_enable_flag
attribute.description: Indicates if callamp is enabled or disabled during image acquisition.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: callamp set to disabled
callamp set to enabled

attribute.title: callamp_frequency
attribute.description: The callamp frequency is determined by the internal 24 MHz clock and an integer divisor. CALLAMP_FREQUENCY = 24 MHz / Value The standard callamp frequency is 100 kHz (24MHz / 240).

attribute.title: callamp_strobe_time
attribute.description: Callamp strobe time is measured in microseconds after callamp switch on. callamp switch off time = START_TIME + DAWN_CALLAMP_DELAY_TIME + DAWN_CALLAMP_STROBE_TIME

attribute.title: chamber
attribute.description: This keyword was used during ground tests to describe the test environment.

attribute.title: data_routing_id
attribute.description: This keyword describes the priority of the acquired image and thus how it was handled on board.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The image is processed with highest priority and streamed into VR10 of the s/c.
The image is processed with high priority and streamed into VR8 of the s/c.
The image is processed with mid priority and streamed into VR8 of the s/c.
The image is processed with low priority and streamed into VR8 of the s/c.
The image is processed with least priority and streamed into VR8 of the s/c.

attribute.title: dpu_hardware_id
attribute.description: Both DPUs for FC1 and FC2 have the same DPU ID because they are identical.

attribute.title: dpu_software_version
attribute.description: Current version of the FC onboard software

attribute.title: fee_flag
attribute.description: OFF = FEE is disabled, images cannot be acquired ON = FEE is enabled, images can be acquired

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: FEE is disabled, images cannot be acquired
FEE is enabled, images can be acquired

attribute.title: fee_hardware_id
attribute.description: The fee_hardware_id attribute indicates the identifer associated with each Framing Camera.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: FEE ID of FC2 (FM2)
FEE ID of FC1 (FS1)
indicates that the FEE is off or busy and cannot transmit its ID.

attribute.title: filter_encoder
attribute.description: FILTER_NUMBER = (((64 + 4 + encoderOnClearFilter - FILTER_ENCODER) / 8) MOD 8) + 1 encoderOnClearFilter is a hardware-dependent constant filterEncoder is the current readout of the encoder filterNumber return a value in the range [1..8]. All the operation are integer operations, MOD represents modulo and / is the integer division. The subtraction is negative (F1 - Fx) because the encoder value decreases with increasing filter number.

attribute.title: front_door_encoder
attribute.description: The Front Door is closed if FRONT_DOOR_ENCODER shows the nominal value +/- 1 and otherwise is open.

attribute.title: front_door_status_id
attribute.description: The front_door_status_id attribute indicates the status of the Front Door, covering the camera aperture, when the image was acquired. In the case of windowed images, this value is the same for all the subframes.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: Front Door is closed.
Front Door is open.

attribute.title: fsa_shoot_enable_flag
attribute.description: The fsa_shoot_enable_flag attribute determines if the Fail Safe Actuator is enabled. For saftey safety reasons, the FSA requires two switches to be active at the same time in order to be active. One of them alone will have no effect.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The Fail Safe Actuator for the Front Door is disabled.
The Fail Safe Actuator for the Front Door is enabled. FSA_SHOOT_FLAG can be switched ON now.

attribute.title: fsa_shoot_flag
attribute.description: The fsa_shoot_flag attribute determines if the Fail-Safe Actuator is active.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The Fail Safe Actuator for the Front Door is switched off.
The Fail Safe Actuator for the Front Door is switched on.

attribute.title: heater0_flag
attribute.description: The heater0_flag attribute indicates status of the Camera Head Heater. The heater produces 4.4 W (5.6 Ohm at +5 V).

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The CH heater (HEATER0) is switched on.
The CH heater (HEATER0) is switched off.

attribute.title: heater1_flag
attribute.description: The heater1_flag attribute indicates the status of the Baffle Heater. The heater produces 1.0 W (26 Ohm at +5 V)

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The Baffle heater (HEATER1) is switched on.
The Baffle heater (HEATER1) is switched off.

attribute.title: image_acquire_mode
attribute.description: The image_acquire_mode attribute indicates the FC mode setting of image acquisition.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The image was acquired with Front Door closed and the Callamp off.
The image was acquired with Front Door closed and the Callamp on.
The image was acquired with Front Door open.
The artificial image shows the readout of the serial register.
The image shows the readout of the storage area of the CCD.
The artificial iamge shows a test pattern with DNs from 0 to 16382.

attribute.title: mcu_flag
attribute.description: The mcu_flag attribute indicates whether the Mechanism Controller Unit (MCU) is powered. It is independent of the MCU motor power flag.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: MCU is disabled, mechanisms cannot be moved.
MCU is enabled, mechanisms (filter wheel and front door) can be moved

attribute.title: mcu_hardware_id
attribute.description: The mcu_hardware_id attribute is an identifier indicating which FC unit is in use.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: MCU ID of FC1 (FS1)
MCU ID of FC2 (FM2)

attribute.title: mcu_motor_flag
attribute.description: The mcu_motor_flag indicates if the motors for the mechanisms are powered. This switch and flag are independent of the MCU power flag.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: Both motors (Front Door and Filter wheel) are unpowered.
Both motors are powered. Either to hold their position or to move to another position.

attribute.title: operator
attribute.description: This keyword was used during ground tests to indicate the responsible operator of the test.

attribute.title: pcu_hardware_id
attribute.description: The pcu_hardware_id is an analog value showing the hardware ID of the Power Converter Unit (PCU). The actual value can jitter around the nominal.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: PCU ID of FC2 (FM2)
PCU ID of FC1 (FS1)

attribute.title: target
attribute.description: This keyword was used during ground tests to describe the target the FC was pointing at during the test

attribute.description: Current version of the FC UDP library

attribute.title: use_pre_clear
attribute.description: The use_pre_clear attribute indicates whether a pre-clear of the CCD was performed prior to image acquisition. A pre-clear is performed 193 ms prior to image acquisition and removes all charge that is on the CCD at the time of execution.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: No pre-clear of the CCD prior to an image acquisition.
A pre-clear of the CCD was performed prior to image acquisition.

attribute.title: dark_acquisition_rate
attribute.description: The dar_acquisition_rate attribute is the number of frames acquired between two background measurements.

attribute.title: exposure_duration
attribute.description: The exposure_duration attribute is the integration time expressed in milliseconds. It is the exposure time of elementary exposures when summing is performed.
attribute.unitId: day, hr, julian day, microseconds, min, ms, ns, s, yr

attribute.title: external_repetition_time
attribute.description: The external_repetition_time attribute is the time required for a frame acqusition cycle (> exposure_duration * frame_summing).
attribute.unitId: day, hr, julian day, microseconds, min, ms, ns, s, yr

attribute.title: frame_summing
attribute.description: The frame_summing attribute is the number of elementary exposures when summing is performed.

attribute.title: scan_start_angle
attribute.description: The scan_start_angle attribute indicates the start position of the VIR scan mirror.
attribute.unitId: arcmin, arcsec, deg, hr, mrad, rad

attribute.title: scan_step_angle
attribute.description: The scan_step_angle attribute indicates the size of each step of the VIR scan mirror.
attribute.unitId: arcmin, arcsec, deg, hr, mrad, rad

attribute.title: scan_step_number
attribute.description: The scan_step_number attribute indicates the number of acquisitions performed within a single VIR scan mirror unit position.

attribute.title: scan_stop_angle
attribute.description: The scan_stop_angle attribute indicates the stop position of the VIR scan mirror.
attribute.unitId: arcmin, arcsec, deg, hr, mrad, rad

attribute.title: comment
attribute.description: Remarks about the containing object.

attribute.title: grand_interval
attribute.description: The duration of the interval.

attribute.title: grand_start_sclk
attribute.description: The first SCLK for which this readout is applicable

attribute.title: grand_stop_sclk
attribute.description: The last SCLK for which this readout is applicable

attribute.description: Remarks about the containing object.

attribute.title: grand_interval
attribute.description: The duration of the interval.
attribute.unitId: day, hr, julian day, microseconds, min, ms, ns, s, yr

attribute.description: The first SCLK for which this readout is applicable

attribute.title: grand_stop_sclk
attribute.description: The last SCLK for which this readout is applicable

attribute.title: vir_ir_start_x_position
attribute.description: This keyword gives the X coordinate of the first CCD pixel used on the IR FPA. This quantity determines the correspondence between wavelength and spectral channels.

attribute.title: vir_ir_start_y_position
attribute.description: This keyword gives the Y coordinate of the first CCD pixel used on the IR FPA. This quantity determines the correspondence between wavelength and spectral channels.

attribute.title: vir_vis_start_x_position
attribute.description: This keyword gives the X coordinate of the first CCD pixel used on the VIS FPA. This quantity determines the correspondence between wavelength and spectral channels.

attribute.title: vir_vis_start_y_position
attribute.description: This keyword gives the Y coordinate of the first CCD pixel used on the VIS FPA. This quantity determines the correspondence between wavelength and spectral channels.

attribute.title: vir_cryocooler_maximum_temperature
attribute.description: The vir_cyrocooler_maximum_temperature indicates the maxiumum temperature on the VIR cryocooler during the VIR image acquisition.

attribute.title: vir_focal_plane_maximum_temperature
attribute.description: The vir_focal_plane_maximum_temperature indicates the maxiumum temperature on the VIR focal plane during the VIR image acquisition.

attribute.title: vir_spectrometer_maximum_temperature
attribute.description: The vir_spectrometer_maximum_temperature indicates the maxiumum temperature on the VIR grating spectrometer during the VIR image acquisition.

attribute.title: vir_telescope_maximum_temperature
attribute.description: The vir_telescope_maximum_temperature indicates the maxiumum temperature on the VIR optical telescope during the VIR image acquisition.

attribute.title: channel_id
attribute.description: The channel_id identifies the instrument channel producing the data.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The data were produced by the Infrared (IR) channel.
The data were produced by the Visibile (VIS) channel.

attribute.title: data_quality_id
attribute.description: The data_quality_id is an indicator of whether data files is complete or if there are missing lines.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The data qube is incomplete (there are missing lines).
The data qube is complete.

attribute.title: instrument_mode_id

attribute.title: scan_mode_id
attribute.description: The scan_mode_id is an integer in the range 0 to 10 that identifies the VIR Scan Mirror mode. "0" means that the mirror was not used. The VIR scan mirror performs, when commanded, and angular movement around an axis parallel to the slit direction (y direction). There can be 10 different modes, each one identifying a given angular movement.

attribute.title: software_version_id
attribute.description: The software_version_id attribute identifies the software used to write the labels and format the data.

attribute.title: telemetry_source_id
attribute.description: The telemetry_source_id attribute identifies the Electrical Ground Supporting Equipment (EGSE) used to produce the data file. This attribute is always set to "EGSE".

attribute.title: comment
attribute.description: The comment attribute is a character string expressing one or more remarks or thoughts relevant to the object.
